member.remarks: If this connection mode is used to implement new G/M/T-codes, always call the command before further actions are started and make sure it returns true before the code is further processed. If the flush command returns false, it is recommended to send to resolve the command. DCS follows the same pattern for internally processed codes, too. If a code from a macro file is intercepted, make sure to set the flag if new codes are inserted, else they will be started when the macro file(s) have finished.
